**PEARLS FOR TRACHEOSTOMY CARE**
Please Note - the internal diameter of an ETT is designated by the tube name - i.e. 6.0 tube has a 6.0 mm internal diameter. If the tracheostomy is less than 2 weeks old, the tract is immature and there is risk of creating a false lumen if attempts to replace or change the tracheostomy are made.

